# Initializing git ( Create a empty repository):

git init   

# Check the status of the git:

git Status   

# Adding changes from working directory to staging area:

git add (file name)    # Add a particular file. 

git add --all          # Add all file using --all.

git add -A             # Same as above commands its just a short form insteas of --all to -A

git add .              # Using dot symbol also we call add all files.

# Adding Changes from Staging Area To Local Repository :

git commit -m "some message"  # -m denotes for modified files

